frontmatter.title: Javascript - 104 | Types & Cast-Coercion
frontmatter.description: Programming languages all have built-in data structures, but these often differ from one language to another. This article attempts to list the built-in data structures available in JavaScript and what properties they have. These can be used to build other data structures. Wherever possible, comparisons with other languages are drawn
